// components/PropertyInputForm.js
import React from 'react';
import PredictedPrice from './PredictedPrice';

const PropertyInputForm = ({ propertyInput, handleInputChange, handleFormSubmit, predictedPrice }) => {
    return (
        <form onSubmit={handleFormSubmit}> 
            <label>
                Area:
                <input type="number" name="Area" value={propertyInput.Area} onChange={handleInputChange} />
            </label>
            <label>
                Bedrooms:
                <input type="number" name="Bedrooms" value={propertyInput.Bedrooms} onChange={handleInputChange} />
            </label>
            <label>
                Bathrooms:
                <input type="number" name="Bathrooms" value={propertyInput.Bathrooms} onChange={handleInputChange} />
            </label>
            <label>
                Location:
                <select name="Location" value={propertyInput.Location} onChange={handleInputChange}>

                    <option value="none">Select a location</option>
                    <option value="Downtown">Downtown</option>
                    <option value="Suburban">Suburban</option>
                    <option value="Rural">Rural</option>
                </select>
            </label>


            <label>
                Age of Property:
                <input type="number" name="Age of Property" value={propertyInput["Age of Property"]} onChange={handleInputChange} />
            </label>
            <button type="submit">Predict Price</button>
            {predictedPrice !== null && <PredictedPrice predictedPrice={predictedPrice} />}
        </form>
    );
};

export default PropertyInputForm;
